18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 11 O.S. 2021, Section 29-102, is
20 amended to read as follows:
21 Section 29-102. All cities having a paid fire department shall
22 have one full-time fire chief who shall supervise and administer the
23 fire department in accordance with the policies and procedures
24 prescribed by the governing body or by the city manager. The fire
Req. No. 10627 Page 1

1 depa rtment shall be under the direction and control of the fire
2 chief who shall not serve as fire chief and also as police chief,
3 city manager, mayor or any other position that impairs the ability
4 to perform the duties of a fire chief. The fire chief, whether
5 permanent or interim, of any paid municipal fire department shall
6 have had at least three (3) years' actual experience as a paid fire
7 fighter before assuming the position of fire chief. It shall be the
8 duty of the fire chief to file the appropriate activity report forms
9 reports utilizing the National Emergency Response Information System
10 (NERIS) with the Office of the State Fire Marshal in Oklahoma City
11 on an annual basis. The activity report forms shall be designed by
12 the State Fire Marshal and shall include, but not be limited to, the
13 amount of property and vehicle fire loss, types of fires,
14 inspections and investigations that occurred. The report shall
15 include notification of all fire-related civilian deaths and
16 injuries in the respective jurisdiction and of fire fighter deaths
17 in the line of duty and of fire fighter injuries in the line of duty
18 requiring the services of a hospital or physician or both and these
19 fire-related burn injuries and death reports will be completed
20 within forty-eight (48) hours of the incident.
